Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.25,0:00:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I must say, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.96,0:00:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have found an excellent property\Nfor yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.09,0:00:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This place is only 20 minutes by car\Nfrom the center of Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.18,0:00:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,BERLIN\N(FORMER EAST GERMAN SIDE)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.72,0:00:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it's in a great location\Nwith good access to transportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.64,0:00:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never find another estate\Nas nice as this in former East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.56,0:00:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe this used to be\Nthe house of Mr. Liebert,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.32,0:00:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,an adviser in\Nthe former East German Trade Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.20,0:00:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You're only here to inquire\Nabout Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.83,0:00:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not a client?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.62,0:00:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but there is something\NI need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.46,0:00:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about a government official\Nwho defected ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.05,0:00:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When Mr. and Mrs. Liebert were here,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.92,0:00:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe they adopted a pair of twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.05,0:00:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.68,0:00:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the landowner of this place?\NCan you introduce us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.14,0:00:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the old East German\Nproperties belong
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.44,0:01:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to wealthy Jews who fled\Nduring the Nazi regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.69,0:01:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Eastern government is\Npaying foreign countries
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.61,0:01:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the West to rent the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.24,0:01:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The owner of this place\Nlives overseas too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.53,0:01:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, our real estate company is\Nfrom the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.03,0:01:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and we only expanded after the Wall fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.45,0:01:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't know anything\Nabout the old stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.12,0:01:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. I'm locking up, so please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.54,0:01:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone know what happened\Nten years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.84,0:01:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Would anyone remember Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.46,0:01:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said earlier, this was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.34,0:01:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the residential district of the former\Ntop government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.39,0:01:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them scattered once the Wall fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.89,0:01:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially those\Nin the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now I think of it…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A former East German Trade Bureau\Nofficial is ten houses down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.61,0:01:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.95,0:01:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't have to risk\Neverything to defect,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:01:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,since he could have patiently waited\Nfor East Germany to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.87,0:02:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get why he went\Nto the free country, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.79,0:02:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He was even murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.63,0:02:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Liebert have a pair of twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.38,0:02:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Twins? Hmm…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.97,0:02:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.18,0:02:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins Mr. Liebert adopted\Nfrom the orphanage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.27,0:02:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.68,0:02:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They were cute kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Liebert always wanted kids of his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.32,0:02:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh… Where is that orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.53,0:02:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Let's see…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.11,0:02:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Um… 511…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.91,0:02:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! I think it's Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.33,0:02:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinderheim 511?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.53,0:05:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This place used to be an orphanage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but soon it will be a supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that this disturbing building\Nwill finally be torn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Do you know where I can find\Nthe employees who worked in the orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.76,0:05:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Employees? There's no one left, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to talk about this place\Nsince it gives me the chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.39,0:05:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ex… Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.85,0:05:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really want to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.11,0:06:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a man named Hartmann who used to work\Nin the Ministry of Health is in No. 47.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.01,0:06:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.59,0:06:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Does a man named Hartmann\Nlive around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.01,0:06:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? You're hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.69,0:06:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Don't be scared.\NJust let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your injury is still healing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's festering\Nsince it's injured again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just bear with it. It will sting a bit,\Nbut you'll get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.55,0:07:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you'll get hurt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.35,0:07:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hartmann."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Wall came down,\NI took in all those children
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.70,0:07:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and became their foster parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.42,0:07:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Foster parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I raised them until they were adopted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or until they could live on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The child in the middle was adopted by\Nthe president of an apparel company.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.14,0:07:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The one on the left is\Nnow serving in the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.43,0:07:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm taking care of one right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.81,0:07:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.52,0:08:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I would call it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Ministry of Health, I spent\Na long time working with orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.24,0:08:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I have always been\Nagainst the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,After socialism collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.04,0:08:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I could help the children\Nin my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.58,0:08:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I am poor,\Nit is not going as well as I had planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they are still much better off\Nthan when they were in the orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinderheim 511 was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a special orphanage run by\Nthe Ministries of Health and the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.52,0:08:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's what\NEast German orphanages were like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.77,0:08:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For the most part, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.07,0:08:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But even then, the special orphanages\Nwere the very worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.15,0:08:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just a facility for children\Nwho had no place to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.66,0:08:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They were children of criminals\Nand political prisoners who tried to flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.87,0:09:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their parents were people accused of\Ncrimes like rebellion or espionage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they were subjected\Nto discrimination and inhumane treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The children couldn't fight back,\Nno matter what was inflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.60,0:09:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That place embodied the contradiction\Nbetween socialism and totalitarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.02,0:09:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In their propaganda, the government said
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.81,0:09:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that they would re-educate the children\Nto become the models of socialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality,\Nthey treated them like criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.90,0:09:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that,\Nthe director and educators were horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.24,0:09:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst ones would
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,even confiscate and sell the packages\Nsent to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.24,0:09:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder\Nwho the real criminals were.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear and violence controlled\Nthe special orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.71,0:09:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was impossible to raise\Na normal person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, that incident happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.51,0:09:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The incident?\NWhat happened at the orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that you wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask about those twins, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know something about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.06,0:10:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The sister was placed in an orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.36,0:10:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in another district,\Nso I don't know much about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.78,0:10:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I know a lot\Nabout her brother, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan… That's right.\NI want to ask you about Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.54,0:10:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That… That was top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The government of East Germany issued\Na gag order about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's all in the past now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be okay to talk\Nabout the incident, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.93,0:10:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan… What did Johan do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:10:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He led a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.41,0:10:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:11:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter. Say hi to our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.16,0:11:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-Ah.\N-Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.50,0:11:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that attitude?\NWhere are your manners?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.25,0:11:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.\NWe met in front of the house earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.38,0:11:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.51,0:11:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, about what we were\Ntalking about just now…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.64,0:11:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I don't want to discuss that\Nin front of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.44,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting late, so I will stop by\Nagain some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to have dinner with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah… Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.79,0:11:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tenma.\NSince you're a freelance journalist,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.63,0:11:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you will write an article about the things\Nyou're researching, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.13,0:11:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ye… Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.88,0:11:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.76,0:11:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you write down this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.97,0:12:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The growth of a child depends entirely\Non the adult raising him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.98,0:12:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We must lead our children down\Nthe right path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.61,0:12:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only then the children can realize\Ntheir wonderful dreams for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.07,0:12:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what's your dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Soccer ball…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to have a soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.50,0:12:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.04,0:12:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for dinner. I hope\Nto continue our conversation next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.96,0:12:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry our conversation\Nwas interrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I will come back again.\NI'll contact you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.48,0:12:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.23,0:13:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.65,0:13:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.74,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! It's me, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.71,0:13:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.59,0:13:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.46,0:13:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.55,0:14:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.59,0:14:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-What happened?\N-He fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He got on the chair and… Ah! Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.64,0:14:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts! It hurts so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it hurt, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.31,0:14:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.36,0:14:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann, call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.74,0:14:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.03,0:14:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?\NWhy do you have all these injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.04,0:14:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.04,0:14:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Two ribs are broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.17,0:14:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The left shoulder is dislocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he be this hurt just\Nfrom falling off the chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The ambulance should be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.55,0:14:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah… Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.18,0:14:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are these injuries from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you it will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's time for you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.31,0:14:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.23,0:15:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly,\Nthe way you touched his wounds…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.40,0:15:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.40,0:15:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… No…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma… I thought that name\Nsounded familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.08,0:15:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.87,0:15:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the doctor wanted for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All these injuries…\NWhere did he get all these injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.63,0:15:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, Mr. Tenma…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's best for you\Nto start running.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.18,0:15:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When I called the ambulance,\NI also called the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! I'm asking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.85,0:15:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Dieter get these injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.89,0:15:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it matter to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.06,0:15:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fugitive who is\Nbeing chased for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.99,0:15:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose a fugitive would\Nhave a short temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.28,0:15:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do this to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been abusing Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.83,0:15:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Abuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.29,0:15:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you wouldn't say\Nsuch a terrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.84,0:16:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm taking him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After the murders,\Nnow it's kidnapping for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.10,0:16:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you do that,\Nyou'll get caught right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Dieter.\NI'll take you to the hospital now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared of the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.95,0:16:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor will take good care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.66,0:16:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann would…\Nalways treat my injuries for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.01,0:16:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You have all these injuries,\Nbut you've never been to a hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.55,0:16:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared…\NSo many scary things in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.39,0:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I have to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.73,0:17:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Hartmann tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a horrible place,\Nand tomorrow is dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.57,0:17:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The world being a horrible place\Nis a complete lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.08,0:17:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.58,0:17:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.50,0:17:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, a soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow will be a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for troubling you\Nso late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, but we're busy\Nwith patients in emergency now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.77,0:17:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It will take some time\Nuntil the doctor can see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but please help him…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.36,0:17:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-There was a big car accident.\N-The bus driver died on the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.32,0:17:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to ask the truck driver
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.66,0:17:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.24,0:17:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He can still talk with two broken legs,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:18:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to prioritize his treatment.\NPlease question him later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.75,0:18:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, in that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.33,0:18:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.67,0:18:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, sorry. I'll be back in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take good care of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.22,0:18:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, if anybody comes to pick up the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,please do not let him go with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.89,0:18:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.10,0:18:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the accident scene cleaned up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.19,0:18:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the traffic is still bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.07,0:18:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I have to find a place\Nfor Dieter to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I take him to the police,\NI can't go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The sister was placed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.96,0:18:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in an orphanage in another district,\Nso I don't know much about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.79,0:18:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Another orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.50,0:18:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.39,0:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say you have a child\Nfor us to take in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.98,0:19:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who exactly are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.02,0:19:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You came to us so late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.27,0:19:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I'm asking a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.86,0:19:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But that boy…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.82,0:19:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you said that the boy\Nwas being abused.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.91,0:19:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have to know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.70,0:19:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you expect me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.83,0:19:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to simply take a child\Nfrom someone I know nothing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um… Can you tell me if this is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the orphanage where Anna Liebert was in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.21,0:19:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.47,0:19:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.51,0:19:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Anna was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.35,0:19:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Anna? How is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.94,0:19:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.69,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She is attending Heidelberg University.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.07,0:19:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? So she's doing well, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.69,0:19:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna was a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.07,0:19:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing I knew was that\Nshe was adopted by
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.57,0:20:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Liebert, the Trade Bureau adviser,\Nwith her twin brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.16,0:20:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.70,0:20:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.79,0:20:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.12,0:20:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They were really close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.38,0:20:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so sad that they were placed\Nin different orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.09,0:20:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Before they came to this orphanage,\Nthey only had each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When they were taken in\Nat the border with Czechoslovakia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.73,0:20:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they were trembling with cold\Nand walking hand in hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.73,0:20:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When Mr. Liebert wanted to adopt,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he originally only wanted to adopt Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But Johan said he wouldn't go\Nwithout his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.49,0:20:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose that made things\Nbetter for Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the orphanages\Nin the East were terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't think\Nthat we are like Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.56,0:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Inge. That's not the way to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.61,0:21:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.94,0:21:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to the bathroom\Nby yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.16,0:21:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Those children don't know what\Na parent's love is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.54,0:21:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People need love in order to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.63,0:21:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like you said,\Nthe orphanages in the East
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.47,0:21:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,were absolutely horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This place used to be called\NOrphanage No. 47,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.85,0:21:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but we did our best to make it\Na nice place for the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.64,0:21:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't want to be controlled\Nby the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.48,0:21:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, not like Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.03,0:22:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They were under the joint control of\Nthe Ministries of Health and the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.99,0:22:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What went on there was controlled\Nby the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.25,0:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that place was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,East Germany's experimental facility.
